Stock-Recruitment Parameters

Source: R/sr.R
ypr_sr.Rd

Returns a named double vector of the SR parameters:

alpha

Survival from egg to age tR at low density

beta

Density-dependence

Rk

Spawners per spawner at low density

phi

Eggs deposited at unfished equilibrium

phiF

Eggs deposited at the fished equilibrium

R0

Age tR recruits at the unfished equilibrium

R0F

Age tR recruits at the fished equilibrium

S0

Spawners at the unfished equilibrium

S0F

spawners at the fished equilibrium

ypr_sr(population)

Arguments

population

An object of class ypr_population.

Value

A named double vector.

Examples

ypr_sr(ypr_population()) # Beverton-Holt
#> $alpha
#> [1] 0.0006708921
#> 
#> $beta
#> [1] 0.0006708921
#> 
#> $Rk
#> [1] 3
#> 
#> $phi
#> [1] 4471.658
#> 
#> $phiF
#> [1] 1721.956
#> 
#> $R0
#> [1] 0.6666667
#> 
#> $R0F
#> [1] 0.1343839
#> 
#> $S0
#> [1] 1.583806
#> 
#> $S0F
#> [1] 0.1746688
#> 
ypr_sr(ypr_population(BH = 0L)) # Ricker
